==English==
{{wikipedia}}
=== Noun ===
'''natural numbers'''

# {{mathematics}} The [[counting number]]s or [[whole number]]s; [[set]] of [[positive]] [[integer]]s: the set {1, 2, 3, ...}, often denoted as '''N'''.
# {{mathematics}} The [[set]] of [[non-negative]] integers, ''ie'', the set {0, 1, 2, 3, ...}; more precisely, the set, denoted '''N''', being the smallest such that:
#:<math>0 \in N</math>, and
#:<math>n \in N \implies succ(n) \in N</math>;

====Usage notes====
'''Please note:''' This term is ambiguous so that careful authors will define it. Common guidelines are:
* ''positive integers'' are used in [[number theory]] 
* ''non-negative integers'' are used in [[set theory]] and [[computer science]].
====Synonyms====
(''positive integer''): [[counting number]]s, [[whole number]]s.
